President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate the following individuals to key positions in his Administration:

1. Mark T. Esper of Virginia to be Secretary of Defense: Mr. Esper is currently serving as the Secretary of the Army and has a background in the Army, Pentagon, and Capitol Hill. He has served in various roles related to national security issues and has received several awards and qualifications.

2. David L. Norquist of Virginia to be Deputy Secretary of Defense: Mr. Norquist currently performs the duties of the Deputy Secretary of Defense and serves as the Under Secretary of Defense (Comptroller)/Chief Financial Officer. He has extensive experience in Federal financial management and has previously served as the Chief Financial Officer for the Department of Homeland Security.

3. Ryan D. McCarthy of Illinois to be Secretary of the Army: Mr. McCarthy most recently served as the Under Secretary of the Army. He has held various roles in the defense industry and has also served in the 75th Ranger Regiment during the invasion of Afghanistan.

These nominations are subject to confirmation by the Senate.